description: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in equity securities that are principally traded in the United States. The index is a rules-based index that is designed to create a more diversified equity portfolio of the common and preferred stock of large and mid-capitalization U.S. companies relative to traditional market capitalization weighted benchmarks.
name: Nationwide Maximum Diversification U.S. Core Equity ETF
